Task 1: Environment Setup and Target Configuration
Step 1: Verify Tools and Services
Check that required tools are available:

# Verify Hydra installation
hydra -h | head -5

# Check system information
uname -a
whoami
Step 2: Configure Target Services
Set up FTP and HTTP services for testing:

# Install services
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y vsftpd apache2

# Start services
sudo systemctl start vsftpd apache2
sudo systemctl enable vsftpd apache2

# Verify services are running
sudo netstat -tlnp | grep -E ':(21|80)'
Step 3: Create Test Accounts
Create vulnerable test accounts:

# Create FTP test users
sudo useradd -m testuser1
sudo useradd -m admin

# Set weak passwords for testing
echo 'testuser1:password123' | sudo chpasswd
echo 'admin:admin' | sudo chpasswd

# Verify creation
cat /etc/passwd | grep -E 'testuser|admin'
Step 4: Configure HTTP Basic Authentication
Set up a protected web directory:

# Create protected directory
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/protected
echo "<h1>Protected Area</h1>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/protected/index.html

# Create password file
sudo htpasswd -cb /etc/apache2/.htpasswd webuser password
sudo htpasswd -b /etc/apache2/.htpasswd admin admin123

# Configure Apache authentication
sudo tee /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf > /dev/null << 'EOF'
<VirtualHost *:80>
    DocumentRoot /var/www/html
    <Directory /var/www/html/protected>
        AuthType Basic
        AuthName "Protected Area"
        AuthUserFile /etc/apache2/.htpasswd
        Require valid-user
    </Directory>
</VirtualHost>
EOF

# Restart Apache
sudo systemctl restart apache2
